Beautful pictures! thank you so much for uploading them here,
Gerard Gillespie




________________________________
From: jonathan ellgen <jpellgen@...>
To: samuraihistory@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Sun, February 7, 2010 7:25:45 PM
Subject: Re: [samuraihistory] Re: Images of Japan

 
I taught English in Kobe about 4-5 years ago. These days I just travel there as often as possible. Several of my Japan images have been published, so I try to keep snapping away and visiting new areas. Ive never been to Kyushu, so hopefully that will be the next batch of shots.

Im glad you liked them. Thanks for the kind words.

Jonathan P. Ellgen
See my photos on Flickr

Amazing pictures -- thanks so much for sharing them. I especially love

the koi pic.

Ah, how I miss Japan.

Out of curiosity, where did you live and what did you do there?

--RMB

messages.msgSnippet: For anyone interested, you all are welcome to see pics from my years in Japan.  Just visit me on Facebook -- look for R. Michael Burns.  All  my Japan pics are
messages.messageBody:
For anyone interested, you all are welcome to see pics from my years in
Japan. Just visit me on Facebook -- look for R. Michael Burns. All my Japan
pics are public, so you don't have to add me to your friends list to see
them. Along with many pictures of contemporary Japan, I have some really
nice pics from Kyoto and Himeji-jo, as well as a pretty cool pic of a Samurai
battle re-enactor on a train.

--RMB
